# Ways of Working: {{ display_name }}

## Definition of Done

- code passes linting, typing, and tests
- route changes include integration coverage
- service changes include unit coverage
- migrations and config changes are documented
- API contract changes are reflected in docs and schemas
- no secrets or environment-specific values are committed

## Development Workflow

1. implement one vertical slice at a time
2. start with contracts and service boundaries
3. add persistence only after the shape of the use case is clear
4. write tests before expanding the next slice

## Pull Request Expectations

- small, reviewable scope
- clear summary of endpoint, service, and persistence changes
- note any schema or auth impact explicitly

## Testing Expectations

Current strategy: **{{ test_strategy }}**

{% if test_strategy == "pytest-only" %}
- prioritize service and utility tests
- keep a minimal HTTP smoke suite
{% elif test_strategy == "pytest-and-integration" %}
- combine unit-tested services with integration coverage per resource
- integration tests should verify auth, validation, and persistence behavior together
{% else %}
- maintain a full testing pyramid across unit, integration, and broader workflow verification
{% endif %}

## Review Triggers

Request architectural review when:

- auth model changes
- persistence model changes substantially
{% if use_background_jobs %}- queued or asynchronous workflows change semantics
{% endif %}
- a module crosses layer boundaries that this blueprint expects to stay separate
